  <info>
    <title>Managing storage pool using &cockpit;</title>
    <meta name="maintainer" content="shalaka.harne@suse.com" its:translate="no"/>
    <abstract>
      <para>You can create storage pools and manage them through &cockpit;.</para></abstract>
  </info>
  <section><title>Creating a storage pool</title>
<procedure><step><para>Navigate to <guimenu>Virtual machines</guimenu> and click the <guimenu>Storage pools</guimenu> link</para></step>
<step><para>Click <guimenu>Storage pools</guimenu> link.</para></step>
<step><para>Click <guimenu>Create storage pool</guimenu>.</para></step>
<step><para>Select the <guilabel>Connection type</guilabel> as either <guimenu>System</guimenu> or  <guimenu>User session</guimenu>.</para></step>
<step><para>Specify a storage pool name.</para></step>
<step><para>Select the storage pool type from the drop-down list.</para></step>
<step><para>Select the path on the file system of the host from the drop-down list.</para></step>
<step><para>To set starting pool when host boots, select <guimenu>Start pool</guimenu> when host boots checkbox.</para></step>
<step><para>Click <guimenu>Create</guimenu>.</para></step>
</procedure></section>
<section><title>Activate or Deactivate storage pool</title>
<procedure><step><para>Navigate to the <guimenu>Virtual machines</guimenu> page and select the <guimenu>Networks</guimenu> link.</para></step>
<step><para>Click <guimenu>Storage pools</guimenu> link.</para></step>
<step><para>Click <guimenu>Activate</guimenu>or <guimenu>Deactivate</guimenu> next to the desired pool.</para></step>
</procedure></section>
<section><title>Delete Storage Pool</title>
<procedure><step><para>Navigate to the <guimenu>Virtual machines</guimenu> page and select the <guimenu>Networks</guimenu> link.</para></step>
<step><para>Click <guimenu>Storage pools</guimenu> link.</para></step>
<step><para>Click the three-dot menu and select <guimenu>Delete</guimenu> next to the storage pool you want to delete.</para></step>
</procedure></section>
</topic>
